Ad Text:
12 + 12 + 12 months ASAP Start    
Baseline Security Clearance
ACT – Hybrid

 

Our client, a very large Federal Government Organisation, whose focus is on national security, emergency management, boarder control, immigration and multicultural affairs, require the services of Lead Systems Analyst to provide expert data platforms leadership to support its ongoing systems and information management needs. 

 

Duties of the Lead Systems Analyst

Setting & governing the strategic direction for cloud-based data platforms & enterprise BI platforms, aligned with organisational & whole of government frameworks;
Leading the transition of on premises data assets to secure, scalable cloud native deployments, ensuring continuity of critical data services;
Designing & assure enterprise scale data platforms that support analytics, reporting, & emerging AI enabled use cases;
Providing technical leadership for enterprise BI tools, enabling trusted, high-quality data & effective self-service analytics;
Embedding data governance, security, privacy, & compliance requirements into solution designs;
Acting as a senior technical adviser, influencing executives & guiding investment & design decisions;
Mentoring technical specialists, uplift enterprise capability, & represent the Department in cross agency forums.

 

Skills and Experience Required

Experience in enterprise data platforms, data modelling & information design;
Cloud & hybrid data platforms;
Data integration & migration;
Data governance, quality & metadata; 
Security & privacy by design.

How to Apply

For a copy of the full job description, including the application instructions please get in touch with GP at the Recruitment Hive by clicking the Quick Apply button. Alternatively, you can reach GP on (02) •••• •006 to discuss further.

 

